Locating a particular journal

If you are looking for a particular journal available online, use the Full text e-journals list.  Type the first words of the journal title and follow the links to browse the journal.

Can't find it online?  Search the Library Catalogue for print issues.  Type the title of the journal into the Library Catalogue and follow the links to the catalogue record.  Records for print volumes of a journal are noted as SERIALS in the Catalogue.  Pre-1990 issues are stored off campus and you can request articles via the link in the Catalogue record.
